  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/deliveroo/24cca067-b397-4ec8-8fc9-e98620641b02/application",
    "company": "Deliveroo",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "542ad47494bd1d66",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "AV \u0026 EVENT OPERATIONS SPECIALIST\n\nOur mission is to transform the way you shop and eat, bringing the neighbourhood to your door by connecting consumers, restaurants, shops and riders. We are transforming the way the world eats and shops by making access to food and products more convenient and enjoyable. We give people the opportunity to buy what they want, as they want it, when and where they want it.\n\n\n\n\nWe’re looking for an AV \u0026 Event Operations Specialist to join our London team. In this role, you’ll power how we connect through seamless video calls, global town halls, and internal broadcasts that reach every corner of our global business.\n\nGet to know our Specialised Technology https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/specialised-technology/ team — what drives us, how we work, and what you can expect.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the AV \u0026 Events team. We are a high-performing in-house function responsible for the technical heartbeat of Deliveroo’s communications, managing everything from high-stakes live broadcasts to the day-to-day reliability of our global meeting room estate.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Lead Technical Event Delivery: Own the end-to-end setup, operation, and strike of AV systems for live, hybrid, and streamed events at our London HQ and offsite locations.\n\n - Maintain Global Connectivity: Provide remote and on-site troubleshooting for our global meeting room estate, triaging advanced faults and partnering with vendors to ensure 24/7 reliability.\n\n - Content Creation \u0026 Media Production: Record and edit internal-facing video content, ensuring high-quality, brand-consistent media delivery using professional editing tools.\n\n - Drive Infrastructure Excellence: Take ownership of preventative maintenance, equipment audits, and asset management to ensure all AV kit is event-ready and functioning at peak performance.\n\n - Support Technical Evolution: Contribute to AV-related projects and office launches, assisting with system upgrades, testing, and the creation of technical documentation to scale our capabilities.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nEssential\n\n - Significant experience in AV operations: A proven track record of running technical setups for live and hybrid events in corporate, media, or agency environments.\n\n - Technical mastery of AV hardware: Strong proficiency with vision mixers (Blackmagic, Roland) and audio consoles (Yamaha, Allen \u0026 Heath).\n\n - Platform expertise: Deep understanding of streaming and conferencing tools including Google Meet, Zoom, OBS, and vMix.\n\n - Networking fundamentals: Solid understanding of AV-over-IP environments, including IP addressing, VLANs, and signal flow over networks.\n\n - Communication \u0026 Composure: The ability to resolve technical issues calmly under pressure and explain complex problems clearly to non-technical stakeholders.\n\nNice to Have\n\n - Scripting \u0026 Automation: A working interest in code-driven AV systems (LUA, SQL) or APIs to customise modern AV platforms.\n\n - Professional Certifications: Industry-recognised credentials such as Q-SYS, Dante, Crestron, Extron, or AVIXA CTS.\n\n - Advanced Media Skills: Strong competency in professional video editing software and content production.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters—solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Solve meaningful problems at real scale Work on a complex, always-on marketplace that impacts millions every day.\n\n🌱 See your impact, fast Ship, test and improve ideas quickly in a low-hierarchy, high-ownership environment.\n\n🧠 Grow through challenge and ownership Take on big, ambiguous problems and accelerate your career with strong support.\n\n🌎 A culture built for builders High standards, collaboration, flexible working and continuous learning.\n\n➡️ Want a deeper look at how we build? Check out our Tech Blog https://deliveroo.engineering.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
